{
  "texts": [
    "Let Assumption 6 hold.",
    "Then, the difference in the constraint function h(x, y), when evaluated at the two policies π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) and π ⋆ (λ ⋆ p), satisfiesE x E y ∼ π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) [ h(x, y)] -E x E y ∼ π ⋆ (λ ⋆ p) [ h(x, y)] 2 ≤ 2L D M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1 ν.We note that the constraint gap between the two policies π ⋆ (λ ⋆ p) and π ⋆ can be bounded using the smoothness of the dual function D(λ) and the dual gap in Lemma 4.",
    "Combing this result with Lemma 5, we bound the constraint gap between π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) and π ⋆ denoted by R-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) in Theorem 3.",
    "In conjunction with Theorem 1, we characterize the reward optimality of π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) given by U-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) in Theorem 3.",
    "See the proof of Theorem 3 in Appendix B.8."
  ]
